    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-09-06T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-09-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="828"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d828">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">462A.6831/9–650: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   priority</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">
                            <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-09-06T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 6, 1950—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1146. Brit <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> informed Dept Sept 5 UK will not
                    veto Ger credit Yugo even up to $65 mil, but wld like Allies point out Ger that
                    credit wld be “economically unsound”. Urtel <gloss target="#t_niact1"
                        >niact</gloss> 1112 Sept 1.<note n="1" xml:id="d828fn1">Not printed. It
                        reported that numerous representations to the French Foreign Ministry over a
                        number of weeks had been unfruitful due apparently to a lack of an agreed
                        French position. On September 1 the Foreign Ministry finally informed the
                        Embassy that the French Government was prepared to agree to a small Federal
                        loan to Yugoslavia in the neighborhood of $10 million
                        (462A.6831/9–150).</note> Dept strongly disagrees latter proposal position
                    remains to press urgently tripartite approval Ger credit $30 mil only now, with
                    possibility reexamining Yugo need additional Ger credits later date. Dept today
                    approached Fr <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> and expressed hope Fr will
                    agree to $30 mil credit now, stating matter wld be raised Fon Min mtg<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d828fn2">The reference here is to the meetings of the
                        American-British-French Foreign Ministers at New York, September 12–18,
                        1950; see the editorial note, <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note> if
                    unresolved. Request you so inform <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                    immed.</p>
                <p>Rptd London as 1215, Frankfort as 1808, Belgrade as 163.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
